  • Constructor Details

    • ValidationResult

      public ValidationResult(List<License.ValidationDetail> details, boolean isValid)
      Represents the validation result of a collection of License.ValidationDetail items, ensuring consistency between the validation state and individual detail validations.

      During construction, this validation ensures that the overall validation state isValid aligns with the validation statuses of all ValidationDetail instances in the provided details. If there is a mismatch, an IllegalStateException is thrown.

      Parameters:
      details - the collection of License.ValidationDetail instances containing validation information
      isValid - the overall validation result indicating if all details are valid
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if there is an inconsistency between isValid and the validation results of the individual details

  • Method Details

    • appendTo

      public <T extends Appendable> T appendTo(T appendable) throws IOException
      Appends a textual representation of the validation details to the provided Appendable. Each validation detail is represented as a line, starting with a checkmark ("✓") if the validation was successful or a cross ("❌") if it was not, followed by the detail description.
      Type Parameters:
      T - the type of the Appendable to which the data will be appended
      Parameters:
      appendable - the Appendable instance to append the validation details to
      Returns:
      the same Appendable instance provided as input, with the validation details appended
      Throws:
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs while appending to the Appendable

    • failuresToString

      public String failuresToString()
      Converts the failed validation details from the validation result into a formatted string representation. Each failed validation is represented as a line prefixed with a failure icon ("❌") followed by the associated validation message.
      Returns:
      a string containing the details of all failed validations. If there are no failures, the resulting string will be empty.
